          <h2 class="text-xl font-orbitron font-bold text-primary mb-6">What is RAG AI document retrieval?</h2>
          
          <div class="mb-8">
            <p class="text-white leading-relaxed mb-6">
              RAG AI document retrieval is an advanced artificial intelligence architecture that enhances large language models by dynamically incorporating relevant information from external knowledge bases during the generation process. Unlike static AI models that rely solely on training data, RAG systems actively retrieve and reference current, specific documents to provide accurate, up-to-date responses.
            </p>
            
            <div class="bg-primary border-l-4 border-primary p-6 rounded-r-xl mb-6">
              <h3 class="font-orbitron font-bold text-black mb-3">The RAG Process Explained</h3>
              <ol class="text-black space-y-3">
                <li><strong class="text-black">1. Query Processing:</strong> User questions are analyzed and converted into semantic vectors</li>
                <li><strong class="text-black">2. Document Retrieval:</strong> The system searches through indexed documents using vector similarity</li>
                <li><strong class="text-black">3. Context Assembly:</strong> Relevant document chunks are combined with the original query</li>
                <li><strong class="text-black">4. Response Generation:</strong> AI generates answers using both the query and retrieved context</li>
              </ol>
            </div>

            <p class="text-white leading-relaxed">
              This approach ensures that responses are grounded in actual organizational knowledge while maintaining the conversational and analytical capabilities of modern AI systems. The result is enterprise-grade accuracy with the flexibility to handle complex, nuanced queries that traditional search systems cannot address. Organizations often integrate RAG systems with <a href="/blog/ai-customer-support-automation" class="text-primary hover:underline">AI customer support automation</a> to provide agents with instant access to comprehensive knowledge resources.
            </p>
          </div>
